1. Scripts and CSS should not be included via URL.
2. Scripts and CSS should always be up to date.
3. Login and change password pages should not be directly accessible via the browser; they should be properly handled and described by the system.
4. A user should be allowed to log in on only one browser at a time. If the same credentials are used in another browser, the first session should be logged out.
5. The session timeout should be a maximum of 30 minutes.
6. CAPTCHA should be required for login and change password.
7. Passwords must meet strong validation requirements and should not be weak.
8. A “Page Not Found” message should be displayed for invalid URLs.
9. Only GET and POST methods should be allowed; all other HTTP methods should be blocked.
